\exercise{3.3}

Ordering by asymptotic growth rate (slowest to fastest):

\[
    2 \;<\; \log_3 n \;<\; \log_2 n \;<\; n^{2/3}
      \;<\; 20n \;<\; 4n^{2} \;<\; 3^{n} \;<\; n!
\]

\textbf{Explanation:}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \emph{Constants} grow slowest.
    \item \emph{Logarithms} grow slower than any polynomial.
    \item \emph{Sub-linear powers} ($n^{2/3}$) grow faster than logs but
          slower than linear functions.
    \item \emph{Exponentials} grow faster than all polynomials.
    \item \emph{Factorial} growth dominates all exponentials.
\end{itemize}





